en_37645_0	Brigadier W.S Rajakaruna, the newly-appointed Director Rehabilitation of the Army assumed office during a simple ceremony on Monday (21) January.
en_37645_1	He succeeded Major General Shantha Thirunaukarusu who retried recently.
en_37645_2	Upon arrival at his office, Brigadier Rajakaruna made religious offerings and received blessings of a few Buddhist monks who had been invited to the occasion.
en_37645_3	As ‘Seth Pirith’ chanting continued, the new Director Rehabilitation formally placed his signature for an official document and signified the acceptance of the new office.
